Already in its beginnings in 1956 the Polish aerospace company PTA sought accession to the 1951 founded International Federation for aerospace, and indeed the PTA member was already in the autumn of 1956.
The following year, the first PTA Chairman, Kazimierz Zarankiewicz (1902-1959), Deputy Chairman of the International was Federation space.
